ABC News
programme.desc: More news, more often. Wherever you are stay in touch throughout the day with ABC News. We bring you the headlines and latest on the day's top stories, plus breaking news and live reports from the scene as events unfold.

programme.title: The World This Week
programme.desc: Yvonne Yong brings you a weekly roundup of international news from an Australian perspective as reported by ABC News correspondents covering the Indo Pacific, Europe, North America, the Middle East, India and Indonesia.

programme.title: ABC News At Noon
programme.desc: Miriam Corowa presents the latest from ABC News, following today's top stories and coverage of events as they unfold. Plus original reporting, expert analysis and all the updated news, sport, weather and information you need.

programme.title: ABC News Regional
programme.desc: Take a closer look at what's making headlines in regional and rural Australia. ABC News reporters uncover the news and unique stories about what's really going on outside the big cities. Presented by Amy Culpitt.

programme.title: AFLW
programme.desc: The second-last round of the AFLW regular season begins with reigning champions Melbourne hosting Fremantle at Casey Fields. The Demons are playing to lock in a Top 4 spot while the Dockers fight to keep finals hopes alive.

programme.title: AFLW
programme.desc: Saturday Afternoon Footy is back at the historic Windy Hill ground, home of the Bombers, as Essendon host Carlton in the second-last round of the regular season. Both teams are fighting for a Top 8 finish and to play Finals.

programme.title: AFLW
programme.sub-title: Round 9 - West Coast Eagles v Western Bulldogs
programme.desc: In Round 9 the West Coast Eagles host the Western Bulldogs. Both teams have struggled this season and the Bulldogs have a chance to score their first win of the season over the team one spot higher on the ladder.

programme.title: Aussie Bull Catchers
programme.desc: Liz and Willie have just one day to catch the remaining 16 bulls they need to fill their order. After 4 weeks without work, Clarry is desperate to find a bull catching contract. Lach's teammate, Scanner, is horned by a bull.

programme.title: Grand Designs Australia
programme.desc: In 2013 Dennis and Karen found their dream bush block in Clarence, the Blue Mountains, west of Sydney. But beauty comes at a price, bushfires are an ongoing threat and designing a house to withstand them is a challenge.

programme.title: Gardening Australia
programme.desc: Jerry tours a tropical garden, Josh learns about magpies, Millie visits a school farm, Jane explores ways to add colour in the garden, Clarence creates a seating circle, plus we meet a ceramicist inspired by native seedpods.

programme.title: Inside The Sydney Opera House
programme.desc: It's the start of a busy year at the Sydney Opera House as the Australian ballet returns. While a whirlwind of romance hits the house with 28 Valentine's Day weddings, disaster strikes and Vivid LIVE faces a washout.

programme.title: The Secret Lives Of Our Urban Birds
programme.desc: Nature nerd Dr Ann Jones lifts the lid on the incredible lives of Brisbane's birds, spending 24 hours with a flock of colourful and chaotic feathery friends including Osprey, Bush Stone-curlews and the Brush-turkey.

programme.title: Four Corners
programme.desc: The nation-building project that went horribly wrong. Snowy Hydro 2.0 was sold as a low-carbon future by the end of 2024. Instead, the pumped hydro project is now five years behind schedule and forecast to hit $12 billion.

programme.title: Australian Story
programme.sub-title: When Kylie Met Sami - Kylie Moore-Gilbert and Sami Shah
programme.desc: When Kylie Met Sami: She was released from an Iranian prison only to find her husband had left her. He was reeling from the loss of his job and the end of his marriage. An awkward first date led to a second chance at love.

programme.title: Kitchen Cabinet
programme.desc: Independent Dai Le tells Annabel Crabb how she survived war, cancer and pirates on her way to becoming a Western Sydney politician. On the menu, a crispy Vietnamese pancake, banh xeo.

programme.title: ABC News Overnight
programme.desc: The final word on the day's top stories, with the latest news and updated information from Australia's most trusted source of independent news. Presented by Mariam Saab.

programme.title: Media Watch
programme.desc: Everybody loves it until they're on it! Australia's leading forum for media analysis and comment, bringing you a fearless critique of the week's journalism, issues and events in the news. Presented by Paul Barry.

programme.title: Pacific Upside
programme.desc: Melissa Maykin uncovers the stories of people across the Pacific region, from Tonga to Timor-Leste, driving positive change in their communities, celebrating resilience, creativity and friendship as locals tackle challenges.

programme.title: The Breakfast Couch
